sql:
SELECT COUNT(*), AVG(transaction_duration)
FROM sip_transactions
WHERE initiating_node_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT transaction_id) AS unique_transactions
FROM sip_transactions
WHERE source_ip = '192.168.1.1' AND destination_ip = '192.168.1.2';

SELECT transaction_id
FROM sip_transactions
WHERE source_ip = '192.168.1.1' AND num_requests > 1;

SELECT initiating_node_id, COUNT(*) AS num_transactions
FROM sip_transactions
GROUP BY initiating_node_id;

SELECT transaction_date, transaction_status
FROM sip_transactions
ORDER BY transaction_date DESC;

external_knowledge:
Failed transactions refer to transactions whose status has been marked as 'failed' in the database; 
The 'sip_transactions' table stores information about transactions; 
The 'access_logs' table contains logs of when transactions were accessed; 
The 'users' table contains information about the users.

sql:
SELECT ti.node_id AS initiating_node_id, COUNT(*) AS num_transactions
FROM transaction_initiators AS ti
GROUP BY ti.node_id;
